trend_summary: 1990-2020 imagery shows steady suburban infill. Central commercial core retains footprint while parking lots intensify. New cul-de-sac housing pushes tree line outward, especially north-east and south. Arterial roads widened; several retail boxes and school campuses appear. Forested blocks shrink but riparian green ribbons remain, with some newer parks offsetting loss.
notable_changes: Progressive residential subdivision expansion in the north-east quadrant, replacing forest.
Big-box retail complex and parking enlargement within the central commercial/industrial zone.
